Building.HeaderInformation: ! DOE Commercial Building Benchmark ! Secondary school, new construction ! Benchmark V 1.1_3.1 ! EnergyPlus V 3.1 ! ASHRAE Standards 90.1-2004 and 62-1999 ! ! Description: Two story, secondary school, 46 zones ! Classrooms, auditorium, gymnasium, cafeteria, kitchen ! Original model developed for the K-12 Advanced Energy Design Guide ! Form: Area = 23,804 m2 (210,886 ft2); Number of Stories = 2; Shape = "E", ! Main corridor with three wings for class rooms ! Envelope: Envelope thermal properties vary with climate according to ASHRAE Standard 90.1-2004. ! Opaque constructions: steel frame walls; built up flat roof; slab-on-grade floor ! Windows: window-to-wall ratio = 34%, ! Skylights: 4% roof area in gymnasium and auxilary gymnasium ! Infiltration in perimeter zones only ! = 0.4 cfm/ft2 above grade wall area at 0.3 in wc (75 Pa) adjusted to 0.016 in wc (4 Pa). ! 25% of full value when ventilation system on. ! HVAC: Air-cooled chiller, boiler, MZ-VAV with reheat in most of the building; ! PSZ-AC and gas furnace in gymnasium, auditorium, kitchen, and cafeteria ! Economizer per 90.1-2004 ! Exhaust: restroom exhaust = 600 L/s total (1200 cfm); Kitchen exhaust 2832 L/s (6000 cfm), make up air from cafeteria ! Kitchen exhaust fan modeled as an external load to avoid getting double the make-up air ! Refrigeration: Walk-in cooler and walk-in freezer ! Elevators: 2 @ 14.6 kW each ! !
